WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.624 --> 00:00:15.223
Goodnight.

2
00:00:16.280 --> 00:00:17.363
Yes.

3
00:00:18.433 --> 00:00:19.733
Goodnight.

4
00:00:52.794 --> 00:00:53.934
Do you want to...

5
00:00:55.434 --> 00:00:56.633
sleep with me...

6
00:00:59.273 --> 00:01:00.434
tonight?

7
00:01:06.343 --> 00:01:07.374
Yes.

8
00:01:17.753 --> 00:01:18.854
What did you say?

9
00:01:20.054 --> 00:01:21.294
Let's break up.

10
00:01:22.863 --> 00:01:23.994
We should break up.

11
00:01:29.063 --> 00:01:30.104
Why?

12
00:01:34.503 --> 00:01:35.843
I said, why?

13
00:01:37.173 --> 00:01:38.414
I don't have the confidence.

14
00:01:41.214 --> 00:01:44.613
I'm not confident I can make you happy.

15
00:01:48.423 --> 00:01:50.054
What kind of nonsense is that?

16
00:01:51.453 --> 00:01:53.223
Is this a line of a play?

17
00:01:53.854 --> 00:01:55.693
Don't put up an act.

18
00:02:00.593 --> 00:02:03.563
It's not nonsense, and it's not an act.

19
00:02:07.104 --> 00:02:08.143
I mean it.

20
00:02:10.603 --> 00:02:12.374
I really want to stop.

21
00:02:14.174 --> 00:02:17.954
So you should seriously think about it and let me know.

22
00:02:19.184 --> 00:02:21.084
I'll stay at Sang Goo's for a while.

23
00:02:23.823 --> 00:02:24.924
Hey!

24
00:02:26.924 --> 00:02:28.424
How can you say that right now?

25
00:02:29.394 --> 00:02:31.934
You're not confident enough?

26
00:02:33.263 --> 00:02:36.133
You told me to wait 5 years more even after dating for 7 years!

27
00:02:37.003 --> 00:02:38.073
And...

28
00:02:39.874 --> 00:02:41.603
And now you're telling me you're not confident?

29
00:02:41.644 --> 00:02:43.573
So don't wait for me!

30
00:02:44.513 --> 00:02:45.973
You're not the only one who dated for seven years.

31
00:02:46.244 --> 00:02:49.684
I did too. I was in the relationship for seven years too!

32
00:02:50.813 --> 00:02:51.883
But...

33
00:02:52.614 --> 00:02:54.554
why do you always talk as if you're the victim?

34
00:02:56.954 --> 00:02:59.894
Why do you talk as if you're the only one who had to wait?

35
00:03:01.293 --> 00:03:04.434
Because of that stupid marriage,

36
00:03:04.734 --> 00:03:07.964
I had to give up what I wanted. I gave up on my dream.

37
00:03:08.304 --> 00:03:10.633
Every day is suffocating for me!

38
00:03:17.614 --> 00:03:18.843
Shirts and ties...

39
00:03:21.184 --> 00:03:23.813
are really uncomfortable. Did you know that?

40
00:03:48.603 --> 00:03:49.744
You were waiting out here?

41
00:03:56.443 --> 00:03:58.253
It's cold. Why are you waiting here?

42
00:03:58.253 --> 00:03:59.913
I just went to the convenience store.

43
00:03:59.913 --> 00:04:01.283
I needed to pick up something.

44
00:04:01.283 --> 00:04:02.753
It's cold, Mom. Let's go in.

45
00:04:06.394 --> 00:04:07.793
Did you even eat?

46
00:04:08.723 --> 00:04:10.424
I didn't eat so I could eat with you.

47
00:04:47.664 --> 00:04:48.833
You didn't have to.

48
00:04:51.703 --> 00:04:53.374
Okay. Thank you.

49
00:05:15.164 --> 00:05:19.864
This is my first time in your room after our wedding.

50
00:05:20.794 --> 00:05:21.963
You're right.

51
00:05:22.963 --> 00:05:26.874
I should have cleaned if I knew this would happen.

52
00:05:27.604 --> 00:05:29.374
No, it's nice.

53
00:05:30.573 --> 00:05:31.974
It's very you.

54
00:05:33.073 --> 00:05:34.614
It smells like you.

55
00:05:36.114 --> 00:05:37.213
Do I...

56
00:05:38.953 --> 00:05:41.554
smell?

57
00:05:42.823 --> 00:05:43.924
Sorry?

58
00:05:44.624 --> 00:05:45.724
But...

59
00:05:46.724 --> 00:05:47.823
No...

60
00:06:01.804 --> 00:06:03.773
"To Room 19"?

61
00:06:04.174 --> 00:06:05.374
Oh, that?

62
00:06:06.674 --> 00:06:09.114
It's a book I liked when I was in university.

63
00:06:10.013 --> 00:06:13.013
I've been reading it again.

64
00:06:14.753 --> 00:06:16.753
Could I ask you what it's about?

65
00:06:19.994 --> 00:06:21.864
There is a married couple.

66
00:06:23.364 --> 00:06:24.934
They're perfect,

67
00:06:25.994 --> 00:06:29.333
even in the eyes of others.

68
00:06:30.463 --> 00:06:32.903
They're satisfied with their lives too.

69
00:06:33.734 --> 00:06:35.974
A happy and harmonious family.

70
00:06:37.104 --> 00:06:38.213
But...

71
00:06:39.143 --> 00:06:43.044
the wife suddenly wants to have a space of her own one day.

72
00:06:45.513 --> 00:06:49.854
So the husband makes a room for her on the second floor.

73
00:06:51.153 --> 00:06:52.594
Then they called it...

74
00:06:53.753 --> 00:06:55.364
"The Mother's Room".

75
00:06:57.934 --> 00:07:00.263
But soon enough,

76
00:07:01.903 --> 00:07:04.333
the kids start to enter that room.

77
00:07:04.403 --> 00:07:06.503
With the family going in and out,

78
00:07:09.044 --> 00:07:12.813
the room just becomes another family room.

79
00:07:14.813 --> 00:07:17.883
So what does the wife do?

80
00:07:19.354 --> 00:07:20.924
So the wife...

81
00:07:22.054 --> 00:07:24.724
gets a room without telling anyone...

82
00:07:26.153 --> 00:07:28.664
in a cheap hotel far away from home.

83
00:07:29.693 --> 00:07:32.763
Time to time, she stays alone in the room...

84
00:07:34.133 --> 00:07:36.034
a few hours at a time.

85
00:07:38.034 --> 00:07:40.203
She doesn't do anything.

86
00:07:41.974 --> 00:07:46.643
She feels happy just by being in the room.

87
00:07:49.984 --> 00:07:51.114
Because...

88
00:07:52.313 --> 00:07:56.023
the room is a space she can be perfectly alone.

89
00:07:58.424 --> 00:07:59.994
Getting married...

90
00:08:01.094 --> 00:08:04.833
also means that your own time and space disappears.

91
00:08:06.763 --> 00:08:08.563
Being without anyone else...

92
00:08:09.364 --> 00:08:12.234
can make you feel happy. I can understand.

93
00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:15.443
It's a good story.

94
00:08:18.143 --> 00:08:22.244
I think it's also a sad story.

95
00:08:24.143 --> 00:08:27.753
Actually, I thought of you...

96
00:08:28.023 --> 00:08:29.953
while reading that book.

97
00:08:33.153 --> 00:08:34.464
You said...

98
00:08:35.763 --> 00:08:38.163
the only things you can be responsible for in life...

99
00:08:39.234 --> 00:08:41.234
are this house, Kitty,

100
00:08:42.303 --> 00:08:43.933
and yourself.

101
00:08:46.633 --> 00:08:48.704
That's why you won't get married.

102
00:08:51.143 --> 00:08:53.543
At the time, your words spoke to me.

103
00:08:54.413 --> 00:08:58.683
I too could only be responsible for this room.

104
00:09:00.753 --> 00:09:01.883
But...

105
00:09:03.883 --> 00:09:05.324
if you live like that,

106
00:09:09.864 --> 00:09:11.594
won't you get lonely?

107
00:09:15.133 --> 00:09:19.874
Have you ever thought that you might be lonely?

108
00:09:23.574 --> 00:09:24.673
I'm not sure.

109
00:09:26.374 --> 00:09:28.283
I don't think I ever...

110
00:09:29.484 --> 00:09:31.183
thought about being lonely.

111
00:09:33.053 --> 00:09:35.423
More than tolerating others,

112
00:09:36.423 --> 00:09:38.023
I thought it would be better to be alone.

113
00:09:39.594 --> 00:09:41.763
That's how I lived until now.

114
00:09:44.124 --> 00:09:45.633
I wanted to ask him.

115
00:09:46.533 --> 00:09:49.234
Being in love once in your life...

116
00:09:51.433 --> 00:09:52.533
is enough.

117
00:09:53.273 --> 00:09:57.303
If that one love has already passed in his life.

118
00:09:59.744 --> 00:10:01.383
And if it did,

119
00:10:02.383 --> 00:10:06.614
will love ever start again...

120
00:10:07.383 --> 00:10:08.683
for him?

121
00:10:14.594 --> 00:10:15.694
Shall we...

122
00:10:17.464 --> 00:10:20.334
go to bed now? It's late.

123
00:10:22.303 --> 00:10:23.403
Yes.

124
00:10:27.234 --> 00:10:29.643
I better bring my pillow.

125
00:10:31.474 --> 00:10:32.543
Okay.

126
00:11:21.964 --> 00:11:24.933
Yes. I think so too.

127
00:11:27.734 --> 00:11:29.604
Maybe I should have drank.

128
00:11:31.673 --> 00:11:34.503
No, I'm not a kid.

129
00:11:34.944 --> 00:11:36.043
Right?

130
00:11:38.744 --> 00:11:42.314
I'll be an adult. I'll be mature.

131
00:12:32.594 --> 00:12:33.734
Ji Ho.

132
00:12:35.334 --> 00:12:37.433
- Are you sleeping? - Yes.

133
00:12:40.003 --> 00:12:41.104
I see.

134
00:13:02.994 --> 00:13:04.163
Ji Ho.

135
00:13:06.464 --> 00:13:07.604
Can I...

136
00:13:09.633 --> 00:13:11.074
hug you?

137
00:13:13.903 --> 00:13:15.043
Yes.

138
00:13:27.783 --> 00:13:29.454
It smells like you.

139
00:13:31.494 --> 00:13:34.523
Do I smell?

140
00:13:36.964 --> 00:13:39.564
It's your scent more specifically.

141
00:13:40.263 --> 00:13:42.503
I smell your scent.

142
00:13:44.403 --> 00:13:47.234
I see, you meant my scent.

143
00:13:47.744 --> 00:13:50.143
I'm glad you quit being a scriptwriter.

144
00:13:52.673 --> 00:13:53.773
What?

145
00:13:59.314 --> 00:14:01.523
Maybe it's not love yet.

146
00:14:03.423 --> 00:14:05.724
I was joking.

147
00:14:07.923 --> 00:14:10.824
It's all right even if it's not love.

148
00:14:13.194 --> 00:14:15.464
I'm not good at making jokes.

149
00:14:16.604 --> 00:14:19.273
Are you mad by any chance?

150
00:14:20.204 --> 00:14:23.874
Can I kiss you?

151
00:14:25.614 --> 00:14:29.244
Today's the first day that he visited my room.

152
00:14:32.653 --> 00:14:33.783
Yes.

153
00:14:50.803 --> 00:14:54.074
That's enough.

154
00:14:57.543 --> 00:15:01.244
(Episode 13: Because This Is My First Time Visiting Your Room)

155
00:15:29.944 --> 00:15:32.844
(She snores.)

156
00:15:35.344 --> 00:15:36.744
(How to make omelet rice)

157
00:16:35.344 --> 00:16:36.403
Give me that.

158
00:16:40.314 --> 00:16:41.913
You should stay for a few more days.

159
00:16:41.913 --> 00:16:44.283
Forget it. You're not the only one who works.

160
00:16:44.513 --> 00:16:45.814
I work too.

161
00:16:47.624 --> 00:16:50.023
Can't you quit working now?

162
00:16:50.683 --> 00:16:52.824
What nonsense are you talking about?

163
00:16:53.494 --> 00:16:55.694
You know I bought an apartment in Mullae-dong, right?

164
00:16:55.923 --> 00:16:57.423
We can move in there next year.

165
00:16:57.964 --> 00:17:00.464
So come to Seoul next year and live with me.

166
00:17:01.933 --> 00:17:05.203
If you really want to live with me, move to Namhae.

167
00:17:05.604 --> 00:17:07.534
I'm not kidding.

168
00:17:08.004 --> 00:17:11.114
Until when will you come and go from Seoul to Namhae?

169
00:17:11.114 --> 00:17:12.374
It's not like I travel by foot.

170
00:17:12.374 --> 00:17:15.743
I travel by bus, so it's not hard.

171
00:17:27.094 --> 00:17:28.223
Go now.

172
00:17:28.764 --> 00:17:30.824
What are you talking about? Get in.

173
00:17:30.993 --> 00:17:33.393
No, thanks. I'll take a subway.

174
00:17:33.633 --> 00:17:35.104
It goes straight to the bus terminal.

175
00:17:35.104 --> 00:17:38.374
Subway, my foot. Don't be stubborn and get in already.

176
00:17:38.374 --> 00:17:40.703
I heard you getting scolded by your superior just a while ago.

177
00:17:40.703 --> 00:17:42.973
Just go to work.

178
00:17:43.243 --> 00:17:44.314
Mom.

179
00:17:44.574 --> 00:17:46.314
I'll give you a ride.

180
00:17:52.614 --> 00:17:54.653
Hello, ma'am.

181
00:17:54.683 --> 00:17:56.923
I'm Soo Ji's boyfriend, Ma Sang Goo.

182
00:17:56.983 --> 00:17:59.493
- Her boyfriend? - Yes.

183
00:18:00.493 --> 00:18:02.723
I didn't know she had a boyfriend.

184
00:18:02.723 --> 00:18:05.133
She's not very talkative.

185
00:18:05.393 --> 00:18:08.663
I thought I should come say hello to you first, and that's why I'm here.

186
00:18:08.703 --> 00:18:11.074
You're so tall.

187
00:18:11.173 --> 00:18:12.973
Soo Ji is tall too.

188
00:18:13.233 --> 00:18:15.044
What a perfect match.

189
00:18:15.044 --> 00:18:18.243
I've never been a picky eater and liked eating spinach.

190
00:18:19.844 --> 00:18:20.943
Sorry, that was not funny.

191
00:18:21.213 --> 00:18:23.544
Soo Ji seems to be running late for work.

192
00:18:23.844 --> 00:18:26.314
I'll take you to the terminal today.

193
00:18:26.413 --> 00:18:28.423
- Please get in. - No.

194
00:18:28.883 --> 00:18:30.254
I'll take her to the terminal.

195
00:18:31.054 --> 00:18:33.124
Where is it? Is it that car over there?

196
00:18:33.124 --> 00:18:34.294
Yes.

197
00:18:34.594 --> 00:18:36.094
Please give it to me. I'll carry it for you.

198
00:18:36.264 --> 00:18:38.864
- Mom... - Hurry work. Bye.

199
00:18:47.604 --> 00:18:50.504
Soo Ji takes after you a lot.

200
00:18:50.574 --> 00:18:53.473
No way. She doesn't look like me at all.

201
00:18:53.874 --> 00:18:57.784
She's cute and bright, and I'm just pretty.

202
00:18:59.314 --> 00:19:01.754
Soo Ji isn't as pretty as when I was young.

203
00:19:01.754 --> 00:19:05.254
I think you're more beautiful than her even now.

204
00:19:07.693 --> 00:19:09.864
What do you do for work?

205
00:19:10.024 --> 00:19:13.393
I'm the CEO of the company that develops...

206
00:19:13.393 --> 00:19:14.903
social networking service.

207
00:19:15.163 --> 00:19:18.304
Our main service is called Dating, Not Marriage.

208
00:19:18.304 --> 00:19:19.604
It's a dating application.

209
00:19:20.274 --> 00:19:22.643
How should I explain?

210
00:19:23.374 --> 00:19:25.374
You know Ji Ho's husband, right?

211
00:19:25.374 --> 00:19:26.413
I'm the CEO of the company he works at.

212
00:19:26.413 --> 00:19:28.383
- Oh, Ji Ho's husband. - Yes.

213
00:19:28.643 --> 00:19:30.114
You're the CEO of that company?

214
00:19:30.114 --> 00:19:33.784
Yes, I'm his best friend and the CEO of that company.

215
00:19:34.223 --> 00:19:37.483
Then were you born in 1980 too?

216
00:19:37.723 --> 00:19:40.653
Yes, I'm 38 this year.

217
00:19:42.794 --> 00:19:44.463
You're older than I expected.

218
00:19:48.064 --> 00:19:49.733
It's fine as long as you're younger than me.

219
00:19:52.874 --> 00:19:56.673
You're not younger than me, are you?

220
00:20:37.913 --> 00:20:39.084
Well...

221
00:20:41.084 --> 00:20:43.624
- Give me a second. - Okay.

222
00:20:56.403 --> 00:20:58.034
What a...

223
00:20:59.874 --> 00:21:01.844
wonderful night.

224
00:21:10.953 --> 00:21:12.784
I'm done sleeping tonight.

225
00:21:59.264 --> 00:22:00.903
Did I fall straight into sleep there?

226
00:22:03.364 --> 00:22:05.034
Is this real?

227
00:22:09.143 --> 00:22:11.074
How could I miss...

228
00:22:11.844 --> 00:22:14.314
this golden chance?

229
00:22:28.393 --> 00:22:30.124
I'm going to work first.

230
00:22:30.524 --> 00:22:32.834
Have breakfast.

231
00:22:32.834 --> 00:22:34.094
Breakfast?

232
00:23:04.993 --> 00:23:08.334
Onion's not cooked.

233
00:23:11.804 --> 00:23:13.374
Does he like raw food?

234
00:23:33.254 --> 00:23:35.064
(Let's Eat)

235
00:23:37.794 --> 00:23:39.933
(Hwang Se Hee, Gye Yong Seok)

236
00:23:41.364 --> 00:23:43.604
The bus will arrive soon.

237
00:24:04.124 --> 00:24:07.024
(Director Gye Yong Seok)

238
00:24:07.024 --> 00:24:10.324
(Scriptwriter Hwang Se Hee)

239
00:24:16.463 --> 00:24:18.633
- Hi. - You are here.

240
00:24:23.943 --> 00:24:25.014
- Ji Ho. - Yes?

241
00:24:25.014 --> 00:24:26.074
Do you know this person?

242
00:24:28.943 --> 00:24:31.014
(Ko Jung Min)

243
00:24:31.314 --> 00:24:32.453
Who is this?

244
00:24:32.614 --> 00:24:33.953
I don't know.

245
00:24:34.284 --> 00:24:36.883
It was when you left here already.

246
00:24:37.153 --> 00:24:38.893
That person said you would know when you see that.

247
00:24:39.393 --> 00:24:40.963
Was it a man or a woman?

248
00:24:41.193 --> 00:24:42.294
It was a man.

249
00:24:42.393 --> 00:24:44.064
He said he would call you soon.

250
00:24:46.334 --> 00:24:47.633
(Ko Jung Min)

251
00:24:47.633 --> 00:24:51.834
(MY Entertainment)

252
00:24:56.673 --> 00:24:58.143
T-bone steak?

253
00:24:58.374 --> 00:24:59.973
How would you like your steak?

254
00:25:00.413 --> 00:25:01.514
What would you like?

255
00:25:02.243 --> 00:25:03.713
Medium-rare, please.

256
00:25:03.784 --> 00:25:06.153
I see. I will tell the chef.

257
00:25:06.153 --> 00:25:08.084
Please let me know if you need anything.

258
00:25:11.953 --> 00:25:13.953
Please set up the table number 14.

259
00:25:13.953 --> 00:25:15.064
I see.

260
00:25:17.633 --> 00:25:19.463
I think the manager's having a cold.

261
00:25:20.294 --> 00:25:21.903
- Really? - Yes.

262
00:25:22.504 --> 00:25:25.604
Her nose is running, and her eyes are red.

263
00:25:38.784 --> 00:25:40.953
Where are you? I'm really upset at you.

264
00:25:40.953 --> 00:25:43.124
You'd better come home now, Shim Won Seok.

265
00:25:43.124 --> 00:25:44.854
Answer your phone now.

266
00:25:45.254 --> 00:25:46.554
What are you doing?

267
00:25:46.554 --> 00:25:49.094
Please answer your phone.

268
00:25:49.094 --> 00:25:52.433
Are you really trying to end us?

269
00:25:54.034 --> 00:25:55.403
He read it, but didn't respond.

270
00:25:57.574 --> 00:25:59.173
He clearly read it.

271
00:26:00.504 --> 00:26:02.143
But he's not saying anything back.

272
00:26:13.913 --> 00:26:16.024
(I want to get married.)

273
00:26:19.324 --> 00:26:21.693
- Thank you! - Thank you.

274
00:26:26.064 --> 00:26:27.733
I'll go to the bathroom.

275
00:26:42.183 --> 00:26:43.743
How's your weekend?

276
00:26:47.254 --> 00:26:49.453
You look very kind and lovely.

277
00:26:49.453 --> 00:26:51.223
So I would love to know who you are.

