00:47:51.013 --> 00:47:52.214
get inside that room.

550
00:47:53.553 --> 00:47:55.084
I just can't.

551
00:48:11.803 --> 00:48:13.573
You're really here?

552
00:48:15.504 --> 00:48:18.113
It's Se Hee! Nam Se Hee!

553
00:48:18.674 --> 00:48:22.343
See? I told you. Se Hee will be here when I call him.

554
00:48:22.843 --> 00:48:24.013
Did he drink a lot?

555
00:48:24.783 --> 00:48:25.884
Yes.

556
00:48:25.984 --> 00:48:28.754
Let's drink up, my mentor.

557
00:48:29.884 --> 00:48:31.854
- Mentor? - Sure!

558
00:48:31.993 --> 00:48:35.093
You're not my mentor anymore. Se Hee is.

559
00:48:35.694 --> 00:48:38.234
What did he say?

560
00:48:38.964 --> 00:48:40.433
What did you tell him?

561
00:48:40.433 --> 00:48:43.533
Se Hee said that I have to be honest.

562
00:48:43.756 --> 00:48:46.026
All those subjects in your sentences...

563
00:48:47.303 --> 00:48:49.843
are all you, Won Seok.

564
00:48:49.904 --> 00:48:53.073
You don't have anyone else as a subject in your sentences.

565
00:48:53.243 --> 00:48:55.984
So I changed the subject in my sentences.

566
00:48:56.343 --> 00:48:57.553
Ho Rang...

567
00:48:59.084 --> 00:49:01.953
smiles because of me.

568
00:49:02.424 --> 00:49:03.783
Perhaps she and I...

569
00:49:04.354 --> 00:49:07.323
are like the parallel lines that never meet.

570
00:49:07.694 --> 00:49:10.993
Ho Rang is happy...

571
00:49:12.393 --> 00:49:13.593
because of me.

572
00:49:13.694 --> 00:49:17.973
Won Seok, I'll be 35 after 5 years.

573
00:49:18.573 --> 00:49:21.274
Are you asking me to just date for 12 years?

574
00:49:21.604 --> 00:49:26.143
Ho Rang can't live without me.

575
00:49:26.143 --> 00:49:27.884
(How's your weekend going?)

576
00:49:27.884 --> 00:49:30.613
When I replaced the subjects,

577
00:49:30.984 --> 00:49:33.384
the answer was quite simple.

578
00:49:34.783 --> 00:49:36.854
The initial formula to get the answer...

579
00:49:37.524 --> 00:49:39.924
was wrong in the first place.

580
00:49:40.964 --> 00:49:42.763
For seven years,

581
00:49:43.723 --> 00:49:48.604
I had been choosing the paths that made only me happy.

582
00:50:13.553 --> 00:50:15.363
Life is too long.

583
00:50:16.393 --> 00:50:18.163
There are too many unwanted scenes.

584
00:50:19.393 --> 00:50:20.564
You're right.

585
00:50:21.933 --> 00:50:24.533
Things will get only worse.

586
00:50:27.573 --> 00:50:29.203
You look troubled too today.

587
00:50:30.504 --> 00:50:34.884
Some production company's CEO came to talk to me.

588
00:50:36.584 --> 00:50:38.154
She told me she wants me to work with her.

589
00:50:41.754 --> 00:50:44.823
But I...

590
00:50:46.754 --> 00:50:48.993
answered that I got married...

591
00:50:49.924 --> 00:50:52.893
to her question asking if I still write.

592
00:50:55.104 --> 00:50:56.433
Why did I do that?

593
00:51:00.734 --> 00:51:04.473
Maybe you were lazy to explain.

594
00:51:05.544 --> 00:51:07.343
Sometimes, marriage can be...

595
00:51:08.183 --> 00:51:10.714
a good shield in the society.

596
00:51:11.584 --> 00:51:13.714
A shield so strong that it can't be penetrated.

597
00:51:14.984 --> 00:51:16.154
But...

598
00:51:18.093 --> 00:51:20.723
I thought I was a coward at the moment.

599
00:51:20.854 --> 00:51:22.564
No, you're not.

600
00:51:23.763 --> 00:51:26.363
There are times when you just want to be like others.

601
00:51:28.004 --> 00:51:29.134
Life...

602
00:51:30.203 --> 00:51:32.973
needs a shoulder to depend on.

603
00:51:34.904 --> 00:51:36.174
Soo Ji, do you also...

604
00:51:37.743 --> 00:51:39.743
depend on someone?

605
00:51:41.183 --> 00:51:42.243
Who?

606
00:51:43.743 --> 00:51:44.984
Mr. Ma?

607
00:51:48.424 --> 00:51:50.223
I don't need to depend...

608
00:51:51.194 --> 00:51:53.024
on anyone.

609
00:51:54.053 --> 00:51:55.163
What?

610
00:51:55.493 --> 00:51:57.424
My mom's supporting me.

611
00:51:58.694 --> 00:52:00.794
I should give a call to my mom.

612
00:52:08.874 --> 00:52:11.413
Why would you say something like that to a kid?

613
00:52:14.584 --> 00:52:18.283
That's not actually what I told him.

614
00:52:20.854 --> 00:52:22.984
That's what you told me...

615
00:52:25.624 --> 00:52:26.924
12 years ago.

616
00:52:30.863 --> 00:52:31.964
Se Hee.

617
00:52:44.004 --> 00:52:47.884
Men are all selfish.

618
00:52:48.413 --> 00:52:50.783
It's a greed to...

619
00:52:51.154 --> 00:52:53.254
not let go of someone.

620
00:52:54.453 --> 00:52:56.354
You like it when you're with her.

621
00:52:56.683 --> 00:52:58.794
You want to make her happy.

622
00:52:59.493 --> 00:53:03.223
You feel like you can't live without her, right?

623
00:53:04.993 --> 00:53:06.464
But...

624
00:53:07.234 --> 00:53:09.763
Jung Min doesn't feel the same way.

625
00:53:10.464 --> 00:53:13.604
She's not happy with you anymore.

626
00:53:14.134 --> 00:53:17.174
Her life is bearable without you.

627
00:53:17.913 --> 00:53:19.314
That's why she left you.

628
00:53:24.214 --> 00:53:25.953
We talked about it here?

629
00:53:26.654 --> 00:53:28.223
Gosh, time flies.

630
00:53:33.053 --> 00:53:35.124
Hey, by any chance,

631
00:53:36.223 --> 00:53:38.493
did you two have something I didn't know then?

632
00:53:39.663 --> 00:53:42.203
I mean, both of you suddenly applied to take some time off from school.

633
00:53:42.564 --> 00:53:45.203
Jung Min didn't return to school and disappeared.

634
00:53:45.774 --> 00:53:48.203
It's strange now that I think about it.

635
00:53:49.973 --> 00:53:51.274
Have you...

636
00:53:52.674 --> 00:53:56.444
heard anything about her since then?

637
00:53:56.814 --> 00:53:58.084
No.

638
00:53:59.314 --> 00:54:02.424
She cut off ties with all her friends in school.

639
00:54:03.453 --> 00:54:06.194
I think I heard that she went to the US.

640
00:54:06.524 --> 00:54:08.024
You can't throw up there.

641
00:54:08.024 --> 00:54:10.663
Don't move. I'll take you to the toilet.

642
00:54:12.064 --> 00:54:13.234
Gosh.

643
00:54:13.863 --> 00:54:15.033
Hold it in.

644
00:54:25.814 --> 00:54:28.544
(Ko Jung Min)

645
00:54:35.624 --> 00:54:37.223
Shouldn't you eat something?

646
00:54:38.053 --> 00:54:39.194
I'm okay.

647
00:54:44.064 --> 00:54:45.593
I'll go inside first.

648
00:54:46.964 --> 00:54:49.303
Don't sleep on the floor. Sleep in my bed.

649
00:55:18.132 --> 00:55:19.261
How is Won Seok?

650
00:55:20.331 --> 00:55:22.531
I'm taking good care of him.

651
00:55:28.172 --> 00:55:29.172
Soo Ji.

652
00:55:31.312 --> 00:55:33.312
I followed you to your house in secret...

653
00:55:33.942 --> 00:55:35.741
on the day I saw a text from your mom.

654
00:55:37.112 --> 00:55:39.382
I was worried you might be seeing another guy.

655
00:55:40.411 --> 00:55:42.681
So I ran up the stairs like crazy.

656
00:55:46.422 --> 00:55:47.661
I'm such a loser, aren't I?

657
00:55:50.761 --> 00:55:54.161
Like you said, maybe I don't know much about your life.

658
00:55:56.101 --> 00:55:58.971
I grew up in an ordinary family without much trouble.

659
00:56:00.331 --> 00:56:04.042
So to be honest, I find you hard to deal with.

660
00:56:05.572 --> 00:56:09.511
Sometimes, your sharp words are too much for me to handle.

661
00:56:12.411 --> 00:56:13.681
But you know what?

662
00:56:16.482 --> 00:56:18.491
Maybe I like you very much.

663
00:56:20.322 --> 00:56:23.761
Your sharp words hurt me here and there,

664
00:56:25.092 --> 00:56:26.692
and it's so painful,

665
00:56:28.902 --> 00:56:32.072
but if you could feel much at ease by hurting me,

666
00:56:35.042 --> 00:56:36.502
I'd be glad.

667
00:56:38.342 --> 00:56:40.241
That's what I think.

668
00:56:42.382 --> 00:56:44.252
I won't intrude your privacy...

669
00:56:45.011 --> 00:56:47.281
unexpectedly like today from now on.

670
00:56:49.221 --> 00:56:52.121
And I won't act like I know everything about your world.

671
00:56:56.062 --> 00:56:57.261
But...

672
00:57:01.101 --> 00:57:04.831
I hope you to face the world properly.

673
00:57:07.301 --> 00:57:11.172
The way I see it, you've never faced the world properly.

674
00:57:12.871 --> 00:57:16.342
You've always run away or fought back.

675
00:57:17.882 --> 00:57:20.181
Using your company and mother as excuses,

676
00:57:23.051 --> 00:57:25.491
you've always blamed the world.

677
00:57:25.951 --> 00:57:28.692
I believe that you need to face the world...

678
00:57:29.462 --> 00:57:32.862
and say what you want to say at least for once in your life.

679
00:57:33.831 --> 00:57:35.331
And once you begin,

680
00:57:36.502 --> 00:57:39.402
I'm ready to support you by your side.

681
00:57:40.072 --> 00:57:41.172
Do you understand?

682
00:57:47.982 --> 00:57:50.312
That was so charismatic.

683
00:57:54.681 --> 00:57:58.092
I'm a bit scared to be scolded by you twice a day,

684
00:57:58.792 --> 00:58:01.221
so I'll stop here and fall back.

685
00:58:01.592 --> 00:58:03.592
I'll see you later, Soo Ji.

686
00:58:03.991 --> 00:58:05.192
Bye.

687
00:58:05.761 --> 00:58:08.801
Gosh, Soo Ji is the scariest in the world.

688
00:58:24.982 --> 00:58:27.851
He's so unpredictable.

689
00:58:38.192 --> 00:58:42.062
Everyone has Room 19 of their own.

690
00:58:45.572 --> 00:58:49.402
No matter how close they are with others, they don't want them...

691
00:58:49.942 --> 00:58:51.141
to find out about that room.

692
00:59:01.522 --> 00:59:02.652
By the way,

693
00:59:03.451 --> 00:59:06.822
why do you keep sitting on the floor?

694
00:59:07.051 --> 00:59:08.221
What?

695
00:59:11.761 --> 00:59:14.601
I'm used to sitting on the floor.

696
00:59:15.132 --> 00:59:16.502
I feel more comfortable this way.

697
00:59:16.862 --> 00:59:19.732
But why did you sit on the sofa before?

698
00:59:23.502 --> 00:59:25.212
Then I felt...

699
00:59:26.741 --> 00:59:29.281
a little uncomfortable in this house.

700
00:59:30.911 --> 00:59:32.112
You too.

701
00:59:32.212 --> 00:59:34.451
You felt uncomfortable around me?

702
00:59:41.422 --> 00:59:43.062
No matter how comfortable they feel around others,

703
00:59:44.391 --> 00:59:47.431
they can't invite those others to that room.

704
00:59:49.431 --> 00:59:51.232
- Goodnight. - Thanks.

705
00:59:51.701 --> 00:59:52.801
You too.

706
00:59:56.471 --> 00:59:58.672
I forgot to give this back to you.

707
00:59:59.641 --> 01:00:01.081
Oh, right.

708
01:00:02.011 --> 01:00:03.542
Well, Ji Ho.

709
01:00:04.081 --> 01:00:05.181
Yes?

710
01:00:05.752 --> 01:00:07.451
About the offer...

711
01:00:08.252 --> 01:00:10.051
I don't know much about it,

712
01:00:10.721 --> 01:00:14.522
but you're not hesitating because of our marriage, are you?

713
01:00:15.621 --> 01:00:17.991
- What? - By any chance,

714
01:00:18.292 --> 01:00:19.962
if this marriage...

715
01:00:21.261 --> 01:00:24.002
is in the way to your future...

716
01:00:24.931 --> 01:00:26.572
I hope you don't hesitate because of it.

717
01:00:28.101 --> 01:00:29.801
Like I promised,

718
01:00:30.911 --> 01:00:32.411
I don't want to...

719
01:00:33.672 --> 01:00:35.442
cause any harm to you.

720
01:00:40.281 --> 01:00:41.322
Okay.

721
01:00:42.422 --> 01:00:45.792
I understand what you mean.

722
01:00:47.962 --> 01:00:48.991
Okay.

723
01:01:01.942 --> 01:01:05.371
Maybe both he and I...

724
01:01:08.942 --> 01:01:11.181
(Ko Jung Min)

725
01:01:12.152 --> 01:01:16.351
need to take a rest in our own Room 19 today.

726
01:01:26.491 --> 01:01:29.862
(Scripts)

727
01:01:45.551 --> 01:01:48.422
Ho Rang, what do you want to have for breakfast?

728
01:02:13.572 --> 01:02:14.781
You were home.

729
01:02:16.511 --> 01:02:18.752
I'm just dropping by. I need to pack my things.

730
01:02:20.181 --> 01:02:21.851
Why are you packing?

731
01:02:21.851 --> 01:02:23.181
I just need to move out.

732
01:02:23.882 --> 01:02:25.451
I thought about that too.

733
01:02:26.322 --> 01:02:28.362
But I think I should move out.

734
01:02:29.161 --> 01:02:30.721
You should stay here.

735
01:02:33.062 --> 01:02:36.761
Why are you moving out? You paid for the key money too.

736
01:02:38.672 --> 01:02:39.772
Let's talk about that later.

737
01:02:40.431 --> 01:02:43.701
You can give that back to me at the end of the contract.

738
01:02:58.322 --> 01:02:59.422
Ho Rang.

739
01:03:05.031 --> 01:03:06.132
Are you...

740
01:03:08.201 --> 01:03:09.402
okay?

741
01:03:13.402 --> 01:03:14.502
I'm fine.

742
01:03:15.971 --> 01:03:18.342
I feel a lot better.

743
01:03:20.612 --> 01:03:22.842
I'm glad to hear that.

744
01:03:26.312 --> 01:03:27.411
I'm leaving.

745
01:03:42.402 --> 01:03:43.601
You are right.

746
01:03:46.172 --> 01:03:47.301
I should be...

747
01:03:49.042 --> 01:03:50.301
honest to myself.

748
01:03:51.511 --> 01:03:52.971
I'm going to try that from now on.

749
01:04:45.962 --> 01:04:47.362
(MY Entertainment)

750
01:04:47.362 --> 01:04:51.272
It's time to be honest to myself.

751
01:04:52.132 --> 01:04:53.232
Please come this way.

752
01:05:01.741 --> 01:05:02.842
Yes?

753
01:05:16.079 --> 01:05:18.020
I want to write.

754
01:05:19.719 --> 01:05:21.820
I want to write something good.

755
01:05:23.159 --> 01:05:25.829
I'm not sure...

756
01:05:26.759 --> 01:05:28.599
what you want yet.

757
01:05:30.969 --> 01:05:35.139
But I want to write a good story that I can talk about.

758
01:05:36.540 --> 01:05:39.009
That's what I want.

759
01:05:39.869 --> 01:05:42.440
You just need to write your own script with your own story.

760
01:05:46.750 --> 01:05:51.290
But I need to sort out one thing before that.

761
01:05:52.790 --> 01:05:53.889
What is it?

762
01:05:57.389 --> 01:06:00.060
Are you already under a contract?

763
01:06:00.960 --> 01:06:02.130
No, that's not it.

764
01:06:02.929 --> 01:06:05.670
There's a reason why I quit my job.

765
01:06:08.840 --> 01:06:10.969
I was almost raped...

766
01:06:12.509 --> 01:06:14.540
by the assistant director I was working with.

767
01:06:22.080 --> 01:06:24.080
That's what I want to deal with first.

768
01:06:25.650 --> 01:06:29.259
I think I can write after that.

769
01:06:31.959 --> 01:06:33.589
If that's the case,

770
01:06:35.730 --> 01:06:36.999
we should do that.

771
01:06:38.030 --> 01:06:40.330
How would you like to sort it out?

772
01:06:40.469 --> 01:06:42.900
I want to talk about it with you. That's why I'm here today.

773
01:06:43.900 --> 01:06:47.469
I don't know any options.

774
01:06:48.410 --> 01:06:51.209
There are possibly two ways to take care of this.

775
01:06:51.509 --> 01:06:53.910
It's a bit complicated, but we can just sue him.

776
01:06:54.480 --> 01:06:55.620
Or...

777
01:06:56.480 --> 01:06:58.349
we can simply get rid of him.

778
01:07:00.419 --> 01:07:02.160
- Do we get rid of him? - Yes.

779
01:07:02.320 --> 01:07:04.429
I prefer the latter option.

780
01:07:04.929 --> 01:07:06.889
My employees are good at that.

781
01:07:07.560 --> 01:07:10.429
What do they do?

782
01:07:11.230 --> 01:07:15.999
We can just shock him to death,

783
01:07:16.370 --> 01:07:18.770
or he will die because of his funny situation.

784
01:07:19.039 --> 01:07:22.339
Sometimes, they die because of how frustrating it is.

785
01:07:29.249 --> 01:07:30.889
It's just a joke.

786
01:07:30.889 --> 01:07:32.650
Let's talk about it over lunch.

787
01:07:33.620 --> 01:07:34.719
Okay.

788
01:07:36.459 --> 01:07:39.759
By the way,

789
01:07:40.289 --> 01:07:42.900
you are really not good at making jokes.

790
01:07:45.330 --> 01:07:48.570
Many people said that's my charm.

791
01:07:49.240 --> 01:07:50.339
I see.

792
01:07:56.110 --> 01:07:58.009
- I'm here. - You are!

793
01:08:09.690 --> 01:08:11.860
They don't have a menu.

794
01:08:11.860 --> 01:08:14.089
Do you want me to surprise you?

795
01:08:14.089 --> 01:08:15.560
Of course.

796
01:08:15.730 --> 01:08:18.770
Can I have pajeon and golbaengi soup?

797
01:08:18.770 --> 01:08:20.129
We also want three bottles of makgeolli.

798
01:08:21.200 --> 01:08:22.370
Three bottles?

799
01:08:24.039 --> 01:08:25.139
I'm sorry.

800
01:08:25.139 --> 01:08:27.270
We want four bottles.

801
01:08:32.009 --> 01:08:33.110
Cheers!

802
01:08:41.060 --> 01:08:43.759
You are really enjoying it.

803
01:08:46.030 --> 01:08:47.730
I am today.

804
01:08:48.360 --> 01:08:49.799
I haven't drank for a while.

805
01:08:50.030 --> 01:08:52.169
Do you not drink with your husband?

806
01:08:53.129 --> 01:08:55.139
My husband?

807
01:08:57.339 --> 01:09:00.669
We only drink beer while watching soccer.

808
01:09:02.910 --> 01:09:05.110
He's pretty weird.

809
01:09:05.849 --> 01:09:08.349
I haven't seen him drunk once.

810
01:09:08.650 --> 01:09:11.950
I guess you guys are being careful with each other.

811
01:09:12.450 --> 01:09:15.419
Yes, that's how we are.

812
01:09:16.360 --> 01:09:21.060
We have each other's "The Room 19".

813
01:09:22.030 --> 01:09:24.499
- "The Room 19"? - Yes.

814
01:09:25.730 --> 01:09:29.400
It's each other's own space. It can't be invaded.

815
01:09:31.509 --> 01:09:33.469
That sounds great.

816
01:09:34.580 --> 01:09:36.639
- Do you really think so? - Of course.

817
01:09:37.310 --> 01:09:39.679
Even though you are married, you need that.

818
01:09:40.209 --> 01:09:43.150
If you love each other, you need to be more careful.

819
01:09:48.560 --> 01:09:52.560
Why are you not married?

820
01:09:52.860 --> 01:09:54.799
Are you talking about me?

821
01:09:55.799 --> 01:09:56.900
Yes.

822
01:09:57.459 --> 01:10:00.629
I mean, you are very attractive and strong.

823
01:10:01.400 --> 01:10:03.700
So I am curious why you are still single.

